cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.SE, cs.PL

This paper deals with natural language processing and program synthesis, which are both sub-fields of computer science. The use of neural networks and semantic parsing suggests that cs.CL (Computation and Language) is a likely category. Additionally, the use of program synthesis techniques suggests that cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) are also likely categories. The focus on real-world regular expressions and the use of examples suggests that cs.SE (Software Engineering) is a possible category. Finally, the use of sketches to represent incomplete regular expressions suggests that cs.PL (Programming Languages) is a possible category.
